# Infrastructure

## Scope

Applies to files in `infra/**`.

## Environments

| Target | Purpose | Location |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `infra/debian-vps/` | Main orchestration server (Docker Compose) | Debian 12 VPS |
| `infra/droplet-admin/` | DigitalOcean droplet with Caddy reverse proxy | DigitalOcean |
| `infra/mac-mini/` | Execution node: Ollama, Agent Zero runtimes | Local Mac Mini |

## Docker Compose Services (debian-vps)

- **LiNKaios** — Control plane (Node.js, port 4000)
- **LiNKautowork** — n8n automation engine (port 5678)
- **nats** — JetStream message bus (ports 4222, 8222)
- **agent-zero** — Worker agent (upstream profile, port 50001)
- **paperclip-upstream** — Orchestration core (upstream profile, port 3100)
- **openclaw-gateway** — Manager agent gateway (upstream profile, port 4141)
- **linkboard** — LLM Council (upstream profile, port 3200)

## Security Baseline

- UFW enabled with least-privilege ports.
- Tailscale for private service-to-service links.
- No ports exposed publicly unless through Caddy reverse proxy with TLS.
- Secrets loaded from GSM (Google Secret Manager), not hardcoded.

## Caddy (droplet-admin)

- Reverse proxy with automatic TLS termination.
- Supabase-authenticated operator gateway pattern.
- Config in `infra/droplet-admin/control-plane/Caddyfile`.

## Rules

- Never hardcode secrets in Docker Compose files, Caddyfiles, or scripts.
- Use `${ENV_VAR}` references and `.env` files (which are gitignored).
- When modifying Docker Compose, preserve the upstream profile separation.
- When modifying Caddy config, test TLS and proxy behavior before deploying.
- Bootstrap and deploy scripts must be idempotent (safe to re-run).
